Man Arrested by Strathclyde Police After Paint Thrown at Clegg

-- B y   K a t i e   L i n s e l l
-- 
2011-08-25T23:59:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/man-arrested-by-strathclyde-police-after-paint-thrown-at-clegg.html
A 22-year-old man was arrested by
Strathclyde Police for an “alleged breach of the peace and
police assault” in Glasgow yesterday, police spokesman Jim
Telford said by telephone. The incident took place at Woodside
Halls at around 5:45 p.m. local time and police expect the man
to appear at the Glasgow Sheriff Court today, Telford said.
Stuart Rodger, a 22-year-old politics student was arrested after
U.K. Deputy Prime Minister  Nick Clegg  was attacked with an egg
filled with blue paint as he arrived at the Glasgow venue for a
party meeting, the  Daily Telegraph  reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katie Linsell in London at 
